      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) match simulated boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FDA experimental data collected at controlled temperature (37 ± 0.5°C), flow rates measured by Coriolis meter (±0.5% accuracy). Boundary conditions in CFD model set to match experimental means. Fluid viscosity and density matched to bovine blood properties used in experiments."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation metric u_val) computed and within acceptable range for pressure rise and hemolysis index.",
      "rationale": "Pressure rise predictions within 4.1% of experimental mean across all 5 operating points. Relative hemolysis index predictions within experimental uncertainty band for 4 of 5 conditions. One outlier condition (6 L/min, 2800 RPM) within 12% — attributed to turbulence model limitations at high shear rates, documented as model form uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
